_:N7c10378800d44829b4ca2bed03a0fbeb <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>The permanent members of the committee are all influential voices within the UK’s Black, Asian and Minority Ethnic (BAME) communities and many of us have a direct personal connection to the Windrush generation.</p>\n\n<p>The committee is supported by a secretariat from the Department for Levelling Up, Housing and Communities.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"permanent-members\">Permanent members</h2>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Baroness Floella Benjamin, Chair, Liberal Democrat peer and former broadcaster and television presenter</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Paulette Simpson, Deputy Chair, executive director of The Voice, Britain’s leading black newspaper</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Rev Rose Hudson-Wilkin, Chaplain to the speaker of the House of Commons</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Tim Campbell MBE, entrepreneur and winner of the first series of BBC’s The Apprentice</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Geoff Thompson MBE, educationist and founder of the Youth Charter</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Sir Ken Olisa, businessman and philanthropist and current Lord Lieutenant of Greater London</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Ansel Wong, cultural activist, former chair of the Notting Hill Carnival board</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>George ‘George the Poet’ Mpanga, spoken word artist and social commentator</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Simon Frederick, artist, photographer and filmmaker. Well known for documentaries and exhibitions such as Black is the New Black</p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n</div>" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
